{
  "texts": [
    "Stability during the training process is further improved by integrating a batch normalization module at the end of each residual block.",
    "By employing these residual blocks and shortcut connections, the architecture achieves enhanced performance, effectively addressing the gradient vanishing problem.",
    "The model employs the ReLU activation function and utilizes 64 filters in each of its 12 residual blocks, optimizing both performance and efficiency in hyperspectral image reconstruction.",
    "However, the model's practical value remains uncertain, as it has only been tested on the researchers' own dataset.",
    "The SREfficientNet architecture, leveraging the CNN, is designed to overcome specific challenges in hyperspectral imaging, such as limited data availability and differences in response functions across hyperspectral sensors (Can and Timofte 2018)."
  ]
}